cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as geometric feature matching, optical flow, and 2D/3D geometric correspondences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks and metric learning, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with geometric matching, which falls under the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper proposes CNN architectures for these tasks, which could also fall under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO) if the architectures are intended for use in robotic systems.
